To help you a little more with your research and offer you my explanation of the prices I chose, I must comment that in an AI-created painting what I value most is abstraction, as this is difficult, if not impossible, to replicate and achieve with a machine. Machines do not think for themselves, that is why it is extremely easy to put one to paint a human face and have it complete it digitally in seconds without much effort, since in practice it is only following what it was taught to repeat or copying what it sees with a couple of variations. Anyway, while I would have priced the human face paintings even lower, I think $100 (the minimum offered in the survey) is a fair price considering that the machine behind it has equipment, development and maintenance to do.
